{"questionId":"5275620","questionHtml":"<p>Four identical lamps are connected in a circuit. The current through lamp L is <em>I</em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/a7e37057b6649162f5f3cfbfe88813d25cc989a7.png\"></p>\n<p>The lamps are rearranged using the same cell.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/2cac9db74bafd54be5e9e64a037ef61bd1eadf0b.png\"></p>\n<p>What is the current through L?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>I</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>I</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; <em>I</em></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; 2<em>I</em></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"5275620","referenceCode":"23M.1.SL.TZ1.20","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Four identical lamps are connected in a circuit. The current through lamp L is I. The lamps are rearranged using the same cell. What is the current through L? A. I4 B. I2 C. I D. 2","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"20","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)","A.1 – The beginnings of relativity","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}